<seg id=1> Guangxi Makes Use of US$150 Million of Foreign Capital For Infrastructure of Road and Water Transports </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Nanning, March 14(xinhua correspondent Lu Hankui)- Up till now, Guangxi has made use of US$150 million loans repectively from World Bank, Asia Bank, Netherlands Government and South Korea Government in road and water transports construction, revealed by the transportation sector of Guangxi Zhuang Nationality Autonomous Region. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Recent years saw the speed up of the building of passage by Guangxi out to sea in  southwestern areas of China. </seg>
<seg id=4> Guangxi imported large amount of foreign funds for resolving capital insufficiency and deepening open up. </seg>
<seg id=5> Invested with over 2 billion yuan, the second phase of  Xijiang River Shipping Pivotal Project, using World Bank loan of US$80 million, has already built up  80% of its main part as 50% of concreting work has finished. </seg>
<seg id=6> The second phase of Fangcheng Port Project including expressway between Qinzhou City and Fangcheng Port made use of the US$52 million loan from Asia Development Bank. The expressway is estimated to be completed and opened in the next half of this year. </seg>
<seg id=7> Beihai Port Conveyance Project using US$ 10 million of South Korean government loan </seg>
<seg id=8> and Qinzhou Conveyance Project using US$13 million of Netherlands government loan </seg>
<seg id=9> together with the above projects are all going smoothly. </seg>
</p>
